            <ab>The 16th year of Lucius Septimius Severus Pius Pertinax and Marcus Aurelius Antoninus Pius Augusti and Publius Septimius Geta Caesar Augustus, Tybi 30. Paid to Apion, Nomarches of the Arsinoite nome, through Shpyris also called Theon, assistant, for the tenth upon calves by the priests of the village of Tebtunis, twenty drachmas, that is, 20 dr.</ab>
